Trail, not trale.
>plump, black, lips
Remove the second comma. You're actually using a lot of unnecessary commas.
>you're eyes
Wrong one. Remember: you're is "you are" and your is possessive.
>... eyes up from her pussy, back to her face
Use "and" instead of a comma to bridge those clauses.
>she's looking over her shoulder, back at you, with a grin
You can remove both of these commas.
